Police & private security have fired stun grenades and tear gas on protesting students at Stellies. CAPE TOWN - Police and private security have fired stun grenades and tear gas on protesting students at Stellenbosch University. Students have been marching across campus throughout the day, in an attempt to disrupt lectures. Chaos has erupted on the Stellenbosch University campus, where protesting students have been met with public order police and armoured private security.  The students have been demonstrating outside the education faculty for most of the afternoon. After a violent scuffle with private security, three demonstrators were taken into the GG Cilli√© building.   Angered by the heavy handed police and security presence, protesters are now calling for the release the three demonstrators.